jerry popperq:  I'm not sure what your taste in movies is, but if you like comedy, you should definately watch Kopps (it's like a Swedish version of Supertroopers).  There's a teen drama with an English Title called "Show Me Love" which won a bunch of awards about 10 years back.  One called "Miffo" is pretty good if I remember.  There are some great older movies too like "A Swedish Love Story" (English title) made in 1969 or so.  "My Life as a Dog" is great.  "Angel Farm" is pretty good, there's a less good sequel too.  The old Ingmar Bergman movies are awesome too, though strange and dark - "The Seventh Seal", etc.  Anyway, hope that helps.
